  "title" : "@Nullable annotation usage",
  "body" : "<p>I saw some method in java declared as:</p>\n\n<pre><code>void foo(@Nullable Object obj)\n{ ... }\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>What's the meaning of <code>@Nullable</code> here? Does it mean the input could be <code>null</code>?</p>\n\n<p>Without the annotation, the input can still be null, so I guess that's not just it?</p>\n"
}